ering basket and weigh mixed vegetables into it. Place chicken on Varoma tray, insert into Varoma dish and place Varoma into position. Steam <b>20 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Remove Varoma and keep warm. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and transfer contents to mixing bowl. Add butter and blend <b>1 min\/speed 5<b>-<strong>10, increasing speed gradually.<\/strong> "},{"content":"Add water up to 1 or 1.5 litre mark (depending on type of vegetables and desired soup consistency) and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Sauce"},{"content":"To make the sauce, transfer almost all the soup to a serving bowl, keeping enough soup in the mixing bowl to cover the lowest blade of the mixing knife. Add crème fraîche, mustard, salt, pepper, parsley and egg yolk and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 7<b>, then heat <b>2 min\/60°C\/speed 2<b>."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Serving"},{"content":"Serve creamy vegetable soup hot or allow to cool, cover and refrigerate for later use. Transfer chicken to a serving dish, arrange vegetable tagliatelle around chicken and serve hot with sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["In step 2, replace olive oil with 20 g butter.","Replace chicken fillets with fish fillets (1.5 cm thick). For the sauce, replace mustard with freshly squeezed juice from half a lemon and add a pinch of cumin (optional).","Vary or add vegetables according to the season and your preferences. For instance, add broccoli florets or turnips, cut in pieces, to the Varoma and steam together with the vegetable tagliatelle."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","45m","4 portions"]}